to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":113,"region":113,"country":122,"address":123,"geo":124},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":125,"lon":126},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":128,"type":129},"34733a","inventory",{"_":131,"mainLang":132,"languages":133},"Ancient Greek","grc",[131],{"type":135,"bibl":136},"edition",[17],{"type":138,"bibl":139},"discussion",[17],{"editor":141,"principal":143,"contributors":144,"change":152},{"_":142,"ref":99},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":142,"ref":99},[145,148],{"_":142,"xml:id":146,"ref":147},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":149,"xml:id":150,"ref":151},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":153,"when":154,"who":99},"Jonathan Prag created file from autopsy","2025-08-13","",{"n":103,"url":104,"height":105,"width":106,"desc":107,"surfaceType":108},[158],{"atLeast":159,"atMost":160},40,41,[],[],[164,165,166,19,24,28,167,168,169,170,171,172,173,132],"isic001855","fragment of an epitaph",{"_":5},"centuripae","centuripe","sicilia","sicily","siracusa","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":176,"body":177,"divs":178,"editions":203,"images":213,"handnote":224},"ISic001855. Fragment of an epitaph","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Εὐπ\">Εὐπ̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Εὐπ\">ΕΥ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001855_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001855_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001855.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001855-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001855_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001855_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001855_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001855_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The surviving letters are likely to be the start of the name of the deceased, assuming this to be the upper left corner of the inscription. The slight overlap of the horizontal of the final partially preserved letter, together with context perhaps encourages Π over Γ, with names in Εὐπ[--] more common, such as Εὐπόλεμος, Εὔπλοια, or Εὐπραξία (the last attested at Centuripe in both Latin (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000005\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000005\u003C/a>) and Greek (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003476\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003476\u003C/a>)). Names in Εὐγ[--], such as Εὐγένεια appear less frequent. The fragment is unpublished, as Orsi chose only to publish the three most substantial fragments from the lot of 8 obtained in 1914 (NSA 1915, p.231).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Heavily v-cut quadrate letters, with small terminal serifs. Faint guidelines top and bottom.\u003C/p> Line 1  40-41  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[179,182,185,188,191,194,197,200],{"id":180,"html":181},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Εὐπ\">Εὐπ̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Εὐπ\">ΕΥ.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":183,"html":184},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimil