ast attested at Centuripe in both Latin (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000005\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000005\u003C/a>) and Greek (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003476\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003476\u003C/a>)). Names in Εὐγ[--], such as Εὐγένεια appear less frequent. The fragment is unpublished, as Orsi chose only to publish the three most substantial fragments from the lot of 8 obtained in 1914 (NSA 1915, p.231).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":195,"html":196},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":198,"html":199},"handnote","\u003Cp>Heavily v-cut quadrate letters, with small terminal serifs. Faint guidelines top and bottom.\u003C/p> Line 1  40-41  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":201,"html":202},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[204,206,209,210],{"html":205},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09",{"id":207,"lang":132,"html":208},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐπ\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Εὐπ\">Εὐπ̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>❦ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":205},{"id":211,"lang":132,"html":212},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/s